    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix UL scheduling data copy in eNB scheduler\n\n### Summary\nThe `copy_ulreq` function in the eNB scheduler was not properly copying UL scheduling data from temporary structures to the main UL request structure. This caused UEs with pending uplink data to be missed during scheduling, as the downstream `schedule_ulsch` function couldn't see previously scheduled resources.\n\nThe issue occurred because the function was copying the entire structure including PDU list pointers, but then immediately overwriting the copied pointer with the original one. This meant the actual PDU data was never transferred, leading to missed scheduling opportunities.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/MAC/eNB_scheduler.c`: Fixed `copy_ulreq` function to properly preserve and copy PDU list pointers and data\n- The fix ensures that UL resources scheduled in earlier steps (e.g., `schedule_RA`) are correctly transferred to the main UL request structure before `schedule_ulsch` runs\n\n"
}